summary: Test providing agent UUID assignment options
description: |
    Starts verifier and registrar.
    Uses certificates generated by keylime.
    Set providing agent UUID as hash of public key of endorsement key.
    Start agent, verify registration and check that UUID provided
    by keylime is equal to manual computation of hash.
    Set providing agent UUID as generating random ID.
    Start agent and verify registration.
    Set providing agent UUID as enviroment variable.
    Start agent and verify registration.
contact: Patrik Koncity <pkoncity@redhat.com>
component:
  - keylime
test: ./test.sh
framework: beakerlib
tag:
  - CI-Tier-1
require:
  - yum
recommend:
  - keylime
duration: 5m
enabled: true
adjust:
  - when: agent == python
    enabled: false
    because: This functionality exist mostly in rust agent.
